      <h1 class='title'>Relationship with powers under Part 1</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c301GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_301gc' title='Col. 301GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c301GC' name='column_301gc' href='#column_301gc' rel='bookmark'>301GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03891'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_502' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        18 (1) Sub-paragraph (2) applies if on an application under this Part the court considers that the orders which it has the power to make under this Part&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) would not provide reasonable maintenance for the applicant, or</li>
        <li>(b) if the application relates to a child of the family, would not provide, or make a proper contribution towards, reasonable maintenance for that child.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03892'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_503' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The court&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) must refuse to make an order under this Part, but</li>
        <li>(b) may treat the application as if it were an application for an order under Part 1.</li></ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
